Nebula clouds:

These start off with alpha 0, and increase at 80% per second until they
reach 100% alpha. They then fade at 3.2% per second.

Once they decrease to the new cloud trigger point (randomly picked
between 60%-90% alpha), the cloud fades at 16% per second and a new
cloud is spawned in the same place.

The clouds grow in size by 4.8% per second, and start with a scale of
either 300% or 400% (selected at random).

The initial clouds are set in a grid with spacing 350x230, and the points
are randomised by ±60x40 each.

The lightning in a plasma storm is triggered every 6.25 to 18.75 seconds,
and this timer runs independently per cloud. The lighting lasts 0.25 seconds.
